               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0178QMM">Qǝddus Mikāʾel Märgaḥǝya / QMM</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1664" notAfter="1671">Second half of the 17th century (?).
                        
 Patriarch of Alexandria Matthew and Metropolitan of Ethiopia
                        Krǝstodolu II mentioned on <locus from="2v" to="3r">2v-3r</locus> might be
                        Matthew IV (in tenure 1660-76) and Krǝstodolu II (in tenure 1664-71),
                        resp.
 Metropolitan salāma mentioned twice on <locus target="#4r">4r</locus> is probably salāma II (in tenure 1348/50-88/90), a possible
                        translator of the Coptic baptismal ritual into Gǝʿǝz (s. EAE III, 439).
                        
 The handwriting of the Ms. doesn't look that old and suggests a later
                        date (at least 18th century?).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               </history>
